<HEADLINE> Chinese Puppet Troupe Win Warm Applause at OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The visiting Chinese puppet
troupes, Chengdu Puppet Theatre of China, gave a special
performance Monday evening here at the Secretariat of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) and won warm applause from OAU
staff and their families.
</P>
<P>
C.A. Johnson, OAU Director of Education, Science, Culture and
Social Affairs Department, on behalf of OAU Secretary General
Salim Ahmed Salim, said in his welcoming speech that the
performance of the Chinese troupe "is of great significance and a
great occasion to enhance the traditional friendship and cultural
exchange between Africa and China", it is "yet another symbolic
gesture to promote cultural exchanges and cooperation" between the
OAU and China.
</P>
<P>
"Africa will never forget the assistance and support extended
by the People's Republic of China during the struggle for
independence which according to me constitute the pillars of our
friendship," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Ethiopia Jiang Zhengyun spoke highly of
OAU's contributions in Africa's struggle for independence,
maintaining peace and stability of the continent and economic
development of Africa.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the good relationship between China and African
countries would get uninterrupted development and the traditional
friendship between China and OAU would be further consolidated and
strengthened in the future.
</P>
<P>
Chinese puppeteers performed various programs including
"changing faces", "a concert in the forest", "plating spinning",
"a tortoise and a crane", " happy Spring Festival" and "African
dance". Their 70-minute talented artistic work won repeatedly
warm applauses from the audience.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Chinese Ambassador Jiang Zhengyun, OAU Assistant
 Secretary General Pascal Gayama congratulated the successful
performance by the Chinese Puppeteers and took pictures with the
Chinese artists at the end of their performance.
</P>
<P>
Puppet is a traditional Chinese art with a history of more than
2,000 years. This is the first visit to Africa by Chinese
puppeteers from Chengdu city in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The 16-member troupe gave four performances during its stay in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is the fifth leg of the troupe's current six-nation
African tour, which also include Zambia, Zimbabwe, Kenya, Rwanda
and Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
