<HEADLINE> Brazil' President Speaks High of Mercosur-EU Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua)-- Brazil's President Fernano
Henrique Cardoso said here Monday that the association of the
Southern Common Market (Mercosur) and Chile opened a new page in
their relationship with the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Upon inaugurating the meeting of heads of State and of
Government of Mercosur, Chile and the EU, President Cardoso
reiterated that the start of this negotiating process for the
creation of a free trade zone between both blocks will represent
"a qualitative jump in our relations".
</P>
<P>
Cardoso said that "we intend to cast Tuesday the bases of a
stronger commercial tie, through the opening of negotiations for
the progressive liberalizing of changes between Mercosur, Chile
and the EU".
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, Chile and EU's meeting precedes the 1st Latin
American, Carribean and EU Summit which began Monday afternoon and
will last until Tuesday with the participation of of over 40 heads
of State or government of the regions represented.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur is made up by Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay,
and has Chile and Bolivia as associated countries. Mercosur and EU
hope to establish a free-commerce zone by years 2004 or 2005.
</P>
</TEXT>
