<HEADLINE> Mercosur, EU Meeting Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Heads of State or
government of the Common Southern Market (Mercosur) and the
European Union (EU) began Monday a meeting before the formal
inauguration of the first Latin American, Caribbean and European
block summit.
</P>
<P>
The central issue will be the date of future negotiations for
the creation of a free-commerce zone between both blocks,
according to sources close to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Present at the conference are Mecosur's members including
Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay and Paraguay, as well as Chile as
recent associate, and the 15 countries of EU except Britain.
</P>
<P>
The LA-EU summit is due to open in the afternoon and end
Tuesday in Rio de Janeiro city with the participation of heads of
State or government, or representatives from 48 nations.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur countries are opposed to the start of elimination of
trade barriers from July 1, year 2001, but rather on a later date.
</P>
</TEXT>
