<HEADLINE> African Cities Conference Opens in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The African Cities Conference
opened here on Monday with the participation of representatives of
42 municipalities from 35 African countries attending.
</P>
<P>
The three-day event, hosted by the Greater Algiers Province in
coordination with the United Nations Development Program (UNDP),
aims to boost cooperation among the African cities and launch
campaigns against urban poverty.
</P>
<P>
The conference will focus on exploiting urban human resources
in social services such as education, health and urban development.
</P>
<P>
The participants will seek common grounds for strengthening
cooperation among African countries and for fighting the
widespread poverty and epidemic diseases in the continent.
</P>
<P>
The conference will also discuss the role of the UNDP in urban
development in Africa and ways of enhancing health services in the
continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
