<DOCNO> XIE19990629.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait, Syria to Strengthen Judicial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and Syria signed an
agreement on legal and judicial cooperation here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The accord, inked by Kuwaiti Justice Minister Ahmad Khaled
Al-Kulaib and his Syrian counterpart Hussein Hassouna, stipulates
that the two countries will exchange legal and judicial
information and expertise.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, Kuwaiti and Syrian nationals enjoy the right
to seek protection by local judicial authorities in both of the
countries.
</P>
<P>
Rules issued by either side in civil and commercial cases shall
be mutually recognized, according to the accord.
</P>
<P>
Other terms of the agreement deal with the right to seek
justice from courts, official contracts, judicial orders and
extradition of criminals, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the deal, both Al-Kulaib and Hassouna said it
reflects the keenness and will of the two Arab states to boost
bilateral legal and judicial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian official expressed hope that the agreement will be
put into effect as soon as possible by the legal and judicial
authorities in the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
