<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of the
diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Meets Renowned Scientists
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with two renowned physicists,
Luciano Maiani, director-general of the European Laboratory for
Particle Physics, and Samuel C.C. Ting, a Chinese-American Nobel
Prize winner Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Maiani briefed Jiang on the latest developments of some
research projects in the laboratory. He also expressed the
willingness to continue cooperation between the laboratory and
China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang praised the cooperation between Chinese scientific
institutions and the European Laboratory for Particle Physics, a
famous lab located on the borders of France and Switzerland. China
will continue such successful cooperation within its capacity,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Meets Pakistani PM
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji, while holding talks here this afternoon
with Pakistan's Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, said that China
sincerely hopes that Pakistan and India will ease the tensions
between them soon through dialogues to benefit the peace and
stability of South Asia,
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that Pakistan hopes to restore peace and stability
in the region through peaceful negotiations as quickly as possible
and that it hopes for active involvement by the international
community in settling the issue.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Zhu said that Sino-Pakistani relations
have entered a new era of comprehensive development and that the
mutually-beneficial cooperation in various fields since the
establishment of diplomatic ties 48 years ago has been fruitful
and has had important results.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC Delegation Leaves for Belarus and Ukraine
</P>
<P>
A delegation of the Chinese People 's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) left here Monday afternoon for a good-will
