<HEADLINE> Corporate Executives Get Death Sentence With Two-Year Probation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Two executives of a large company
in the city of Zigong in Sichuan Province were sentenced to death
with a two-year reprieve today by the Zigong Intermediate People's
Court.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zhongsheng, the former chairman and party secretary of
the Dongfang Boiler (Group) Company Ltd., and Ma Yizhong, the
former general manager and vice chairman of the company, received
the death sentence for embezzling and illegally selling a large
amount of company securities.
</P>
<P>
They were also deprived of political rights for life and had
all assets confiscated.
</P>
<P>
He Yunming, the former deputy party secretary and deputy
general manager of the company, and Cheng Zhaofeng, its former
vice chairman and vice general manager, were sentenced to life in
prison, also for embezzling and illegally selling company
securities, and deprived of political rights for life and all
their assets were confiscated. 
</P>
