<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Expels Pakistan Embassy Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- India Monday expelled a staff
member of the Pakistan High Commission in New Delhi for "spying."
</P>
<P>
Dil Fayyaz, who Islamabad had claimed "missing" since Sunday
evening, was asked to leave India by July 5, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The news agency said Fayyaz was detained by Uttar Pradesh
police in the neighboring district of Ghaziabad for violating the
official secrets act.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Deputy High Commissioners Akbar Zeb was summoned to
the External Affairs Ministry Monday evening and told about the
government's decision to expel Fayyaz on the ground that "he was
indulging in activities incompatible with his official status."
</P>
<P>
A source from the police said Fayyaz was apprehended by Uttar
Pradesh police and was brought here Monday and handed over to the
Pakistan High Commission officials around 18:40 local time Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the daily news briefing here this afternoon, a spokesman of
the External Affairs Ministry denied any knowledge of Fayyaz's
"missing."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan Ministry of Foreign Affairs reportedly conveyed a
demarche to the Indian High Commission in Islamabad expressing
utmost concern over the "mysterious" disappearance of Fayyaz.
</P>
</TEXT>
