<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Launches Agricultural Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia launched a
45.4-million-U.S. dollar small-scale irrigation and agricultural
development project in four of Ethiopia's nine states in the
coming year, Ethiopia's ministry of water resources announced here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gulilat Berhane, head of planning and supervision team of the
ministry, was quoted by the state-run Ethiopian News Agency as
saying that the project will contribute to self-sufficiency in
food.
</P>
<P>
Gulilat said some 9.2 million U.S. dollars is needed for
agricultural development, 27.7 million U.S. dollars for irrigation
purposes and the balance for capacity building.
</P>
<P>
The project, from which more than 21,000 families are expected
to benefit, will help develop 5,300 hectares of land, he said.
</P>
<P>
Growing seedlings on 11,000 hectares of land and building 6,000
hectares of terrace are also part of the agricultural development
scheme, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
