<DOCNO> XIE19990629.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mercosur, EU Agree on Free Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rio de Janeiro, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Southern Common Market
(Mercosur) and the European Union (EU) agreed Monday to the start
in November of negotiation on a global free trade.
</P>
<P>
The commitment was made during a meeting between the heads of
State or government of Mercosur (made up by Argentina, Brazil,
Paraguy and Uruguay), Chile and the EU's 15 countries, except
Britain.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique, the parties said they will define next
November the structure, methodology and calendar of negotiations
for a progressive free trade.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur and EU said that negotiations shall be carried out
without excluding any sector and in conformity with the rules of
the World Organization of Trade (WTO).
</P>
<P>
The parties said that the development of free trade between
Mercosur, Chile and the EU will invigorate their relations and
strengthen the multilateral trade system.
</P>
<P>
Both blocks count on establishing a free trade zone by years
2004 or 2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
