<HEADLINE> European Markets Mixed Due To US Rates Fear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 28 (Xinhua) -- European stock markets posted mixed
performances Monday as a strong start on Wall Street was undercut
by sour sentiment ahead of a looming decision on U.S. interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
French and German shares closed one percent higher
respectively, while British shares finished down 0.46 percent on
thin volume of 744 million shares.
</P>
<P>
London shares capped an uncertain session as merger talk in the
financial sector and a brewing takeover battle in the pub industry
failed to lure buyers off the sidelines.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 finished down 29.7 points, at 6405.7. Decliners
led advancers by a six-to-one margin as investors refrained from
big moves ahead of a two-day Fed meeting.
</P>
<P>
Germany's electronically traded Xetra Dax index closed at
5356.95, a gain of 55.74 points, pulled higher by a solid start on
Wall Street and a strong performance by index Deutsche Telekom.
</P>
<P>
Telekom on Sunday priced its 285.9m new shares sold in a
secondary share offering at 39.50 euros per share - the stock's
Friday closing price after it tumbled 6.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, blue chips on the CAC 40 ended just over one percent
higher at 4456.23, a session high. Total volume on the CAC 40 was
1.8 billion euros. 
</P>
</TEXT>
