<BODY>
<HEADLINE> LA-EU Summit Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The first Latin
American-European Union summit meeting was opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Present at the summit are heads of state and of government, as
well as the representatives of the 48 countries --33 Latin
American and 15 members of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
At the start of this big event, the host President, Francisco
Cardoso, affirmed that Latin America and the European Union bear a
common perspective in the building of an international order, as
both continents have common values, share a common cultural
inheritance, common worries and interests.
</P>
<P>
Participating leaders are to analyze Monday and Tuesday how to
intensify cooperation and enhance biregional relations in
political, trade, social and cultural areas.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the conference, the heads of state will sign two
final documents: the "Rio de Janeiro Declaration" and the "Action
Plan".
</P>
<P>
It was believed the matter regarding free interregional trade,
particularly between the Southern Common market (Mercosur) and the
EU would be the focus at the summit.
</P>
<P>
Both the blocs pay great importance to the current summit, the
first between the two continents.
</P>
<P>
Europe is the No.1 trading partner and the No. 1 investor in
Latin America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
