<HEADLINE> Belgrade Hosts International Architecture Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Some 300 exhibitors, including 50
from abroad, displayed their know-how and equipment at the 25th
International Fair of Architecture and Civil Engineering, which
opened here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The fair was of great importance as the Balkan country has just
started post-war reconstruction and re-building of its
infrastructure, economic, housing and other facilities that had
been demolished during the 11-week NATO bombing.
</P>
<P>
Slobodan Pavlovic, deputy construction minister of the Serbian
Republic said at the opening of the fair that the Yugoslav people
are now living in hard times after their country was exposed to
unprecedented destruction following the NATO bombing.
</P>
<P>
Momir Pavlicevic, president of the Serbian Chamber of Commerce,
described Yugoslavia as a large construction site now.
</P>
<P>
At least 120 bridges across the country were destroyed in NATO'
s air strikes.
</P>
<P>
This fair, held under the auspices of the Union of
International Fairs, will last till July 3. 
</P>
