<HEADLINE> Greece Welcomes EU Decision on Balkan Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Tuesday welcomed the
decision by the European Union (EU) to base its agency for the
Balkan reconstruction in the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki.
</P>
<P>
The EU decision on Monday had proved that Greece could play a
role in economic and peaceful development in the Balkan region,
Greek government spokesman Yiannis Nikolaou said at a press
briefing.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, central Macedonia regional Secretary-General
Haralambos Sofianos also hailed the decision, saying that the
decision would give impetus to local agencies to show that
Thessaloniki deserved to be a center for developing the Balkan and
Black Sea countries.
</P>
<P>
EU leaders made the decision on the sidelines of the EU and
Latin American summit which began on Monday in Rio De Janeiro,
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Since the end of the war in Yugoslavia triggered by the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Greece has tried hard to play
a major role in regional reconstruction, and suggested that
Thessaloniki be chosen as a center for EU services for
reconstruction in the Balkans. 
