<HEADLINE> Chinese National Conference on Political Education (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China's
second national conference on its political education drive was
held in Beijing June 28 and 29.
</P>
<P>
Communist Party committees in various areas are being asked to
study President Jiang Zemin's speech for the 78th anniversary of
the CPC earnestly and to continue the education drive, which deals
with the study of theory, political awareness, and good conduct.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and other CPC and
government leaders met with participants at the conference, which
was the idea of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Participants discussed the essence of Jiang's speech and
reviewed developments and experiences from the education drive
over the past few months.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was chaired by Zeng Qinghong, an alternate
member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and a
member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee and Head of
its Organization Department.
</P>
<P>
The first national conference on the education drive was held
in March, when 16 provinces, autonomous regions, and
municipalities and 70 CPC and government offices kicked it off.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Quanjing, who is in charge of coordinating the education
drive nationally, has given the seal of approval to the education
drive of the past few months and has drawn up a plan for
developing it.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990629.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese National Conference on Political Education (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said that, based on experience gained from the previous
education drive, the study of theory should be a pre-condition and
the basis for it and that attention must be given to solving
certain problems.
</P>
<P>
He said that the results of the previous education drive should
not be over-valued and that some government departments have made
progress to varying degrees but some institutes are lagging behind.
The education drive needs to rely on the masses, he said, and to
use the weapon of criticism and self-criticism and lead to real
work improvement.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, some institutes failed to make adequate
progress in awareness of the significance of the drive and of self-
analysis, mobilization of the masses, and the review of clean
government conduct.
</P>
<P>
For the next stage of the education drive, Zhang asked all
officials to earnestly carry out the spirit of President Jiang
Zemin's speech and the CPC Central Committee's important
instructions. Zhang added that the education drive will continue
from top to bottom and will focus on one group and one level of
officials at each step.
</P>
<P>
He said that the next stage will focus on the second group of
provincial and county level officials.
</P>
<P>
The second group of government institutions to participate in
the education drive in early July are in 12 provinces,
municipalities, and autonomous regions and in 60 ministerial-level
organizations. 
