<HEADLINE> Kurds in Cyprus Demonstrate Against Ocalan's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 Kurds living in
Cyprus Tuesday demonstrated outside the United States embassy in
Nicosia to protest against the death sentence of Kurdish rebel
leader Abdullah Ocalan.
</P>
<P>
The protesters hurled stones at the embassy when hearing the
death verdict of the Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) leader, who was
found guilty of treason by a Turkish court in the day.
</P>
<P>
The protesters pinned a letter, signed by "the Kurdish
community of Cyprus", to U.S. President Bill Clinton on the barbed
wire outside the heavily-guarded embassy, calling on him to
pressure Turkey into altering the verdict.
</P>
<P>
The outlawed PKK has been fighting a guerrilla war for an
independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey since
1984. Conflicts between the Turkish security forces and the PKK
militants have claimed 37,000 lives ever since.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish authority has been holding Ocalan, who was arrested
by Turkish special agents in Kenya in February, responsible for
the casualties. 
</P>
