<HEADLINE> U.S. Leading Software Developer Sets Up Branch in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Statistics Analysis System (
SAS) Institute of the U.S.A., a leading software developer in the
world, has set up a branch company in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
This shows the confidence of SAS in the long-term expansion of
the Chinese market, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
SAS has been devoting itself to developing its financial and
telecommunications sectors and computerized manufacturing systems
since it was set up in 1976.
</P>
<P>
The institute began to tap the Chinese market in early 1990s.
Brisk business prompted it to expand the market, including the
establishment of a branch in Shanghai.  
</P>
</TEXT>
