<HEADLINE> Coordination Stressed to Combat Natural Disasters in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Defense Secretary
Orlando Mercado has vowed to strengthen the coordination among
government and private agencies in reducing the harsh effects of
natural disasters, Philippine News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Mercado said systematic coordination and disaster preparedness
have been fast tracked following a survey that showed the
Philippines is a country in the world suffering most heavily from
disasters like typhoons, volcanic eruption and floods from the
year 1990 through 1998.
</P>
<P>
He said the Armed Forces of the Philippines have been
conducting a series of response activities involving coordination
that would equip citizens with knowledge on disaster management
and response.
</P>
<P>
"Heavy rains brought about by La Nina is helpful to our
agricultural sector," Mercado said. "But on the other hand, it
becomes disastrous as a payback of our environmental degradation."
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Mercado stressed the need for the local
governments to declare disaster or Calamity areas within their
jurisdictions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
