<HEADLINE> China Developing Radio-Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China has had a good few years in
developing radio-technology and engineering.
</P>
<P>
At a national meeting today in the capital of China's Hunan
Province, it was reported that China has 1.3 million radio
stations, 26.29 million mobile telephone owners, and 60 million
wireless pager users.
</P>
<P>
The country has 70 satellite communications networks, 5,321
communications earth stations, and 10,000 one-way satellite
stations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China has applied for 43 satellite orbits and
developed 400,000 kilometers of microwave circuits, 5,422
transmitter stations, and 4,269 television broadcasting stations.
</P>
<P>
The country has also had a great number of technological
developments in radio fixing, distant surveying, and telecontrols.
</P>
