<HEADLINE> China Using New Cipher Technology in Pay TV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China unveiled its first cipher
system for pay TV here today.
</P>
<P>
The conditional access system was developed by the Academy of
Broadcasting Sciences (ABS) of China in cooperation with NDS, a
company specializing in digital broadcast technology. The new
achievement allows Chinese broadcast authorities to control pay TV,
thus breaking the monopoly of international companies in the
cipher and decipher technology market.
</P>
<P>
The system will also make it much easier for Chinese pay TV
companies to manage payment.
</P>
<P>
NDS is discussing equipment and smart card chips for the system
with local manufacturers. It has sold its conditional access
systems to over 12 million people worldwide. 
</P>
