<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Exchange Index Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Composite Stock Index of the
Shanghai Stock Exchange hit a record high today, closing at 1,739.
21 points, up 2.72 percent from the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Index has been on a rising track and broke the barrier of 1,
700 points, but dropped below 1,600 points again last Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, the index went up yesterday. Driven by the bullish
sentiment, the B shares reserved for overseas investors also
performed well today.
</P>
<P>
The B Share Index closed today at 61.18 points, which is 2.95
percent up from the last trading session.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai stock market recorded a total turnover of 34.3
billion yuan today, with the total transactions of stocks standing
at 31.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The index of the Shenzhen Stock Exchange also reported a 150
point increase today, to finish at 4,851.17 points. The total
turnover in Shenzhen was estimated at 28.5 billion yuan at the
close of play.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts said that the Securities Law to be implemented
on July 1, 1999 will help maintain the healthy development of
China's stock market, and Shanghai's stock index is expected to
hopefully exceed 1,800 points soon, as a result of the strong
confidence of investors.  
</P>
