<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rise on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices rose on Singapore
Stock Market Tuesday after two days of slump as strong overnight
close on Wall Street buoyed the market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) ran up by 17.42 points
to close at 2,181.08.
</P>
<P>
Total volume exceeded 2.19 billion shares valued at almost 2.12
billion Singapore dollars (about 1.25 billion U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 270 to 88 with 88 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
IPC continued to top the volume list as it registered a
turnover of 146.37 million shares. It was followed by Frt Links
that had 106.17 million units done. Goldtrn was the next with
70.23 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA became the biggest gainer after skyrocketing 190 cents to
close at 14.7 Singapore dollars. SIA 200 shot up 160 cents to
finish at 14.4 Singapore dollars. SIA DBScw00 rose 155 cents to
end at 8.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day
with a loss of 50 cents at 22.3 Singapore dollars. Boustd S shed
49 cents to finish at 2.08 Singapore dollars. OUB lost 35 cents to
finish at 8.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the overnight rally of Wall Street and the modest
buying in blue chips propped up the market gain.
</P>
<P>
They noted that institutional buying remained lackluster out of
the fear of a much higher interest rate by the U.S. Federal
Reserve which is expected to lift the rate by about 25 basis
points after its meeting on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
