<HEADLINE> Iranian President: Defense Talks With Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
said Tuesday that Iranian-Greek defense talks are not against the
interests of any country, but aimed at establishing security and
stability in the two countries, the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos, Khatami expressed regret that in the 20th
century, human beings failed to talk with each other in the
language of culture and logic, but through war, discrimination
and exploitation.
</P>
<P>
The results have been the breakout of two world wars, regional
clashes and numerous misunderstandings, the Islamic Republic News
Agency quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president stressed that the mankind has to take
lessons from the calamities it has suffered in this century.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the ancient relations between the two countries
and the mutual impact of their cultures, he said that the ties
have been beneficial not merely to the two countries but the
mankind in general.
</P>
<P>
Iran favors peace for the mankind, he said, adding that
the mutual cultural and political ties move in the direction
of understanding, security and peace.
</P>
<P>
Khatami expressed hope that expansion of bilateral ties
including the defense relations will bring security for the two
nations and the world population.
</P>
<P>
The Greek minister, who arrived here Monday, termed
Athens-Tehran ties as long-standing, and said both Iran and
Greece were considered to be among important factors for regional
stability.
</P>
<P>
He voiced his country's interest in cooperation with Iran
to create peace and security. 
</P>
