<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Railway Terminal Goes Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo, a port city in east China's
Zhejiang Province, opened its railway customs terminal Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ten train cars of export tea left Ningbo Station yesterday
morning for Russia and other members of the Commonwealth of
Independent States.
</P>
<P>
The railway runs from Ningbo and was originally built in 1910.
It is now twice the length it was 80 years ago and has 19
passenger stations and freight yards that have an annual handling
capacity of 6.5 million tons of cargo and 5.9 million passengers.
</P>
<P>
The railway port will help the city with its comprehensive
transportation network for ground, marine, and air transport. The
port will handle custom procedure for imports and exports from and
to Russia, Vietnam, Mongolia, and many other countries. 
</P>
