<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Land Sales Raise 779 Million HK Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Lands Department of the Hong
Kong government sold three residential lots Tuesday for a total of
779 million HK dollars (about 100 million U.S. dollars) amid an
upturn of the property market in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The three lots, with one located in the Hong Kong Island and
the other two in the "New Territories," were all sold at prices
well above those at the bid opening.
</P>
<P>
Rare among a limited supply of luxury residential plots in Hong
Kong, the site at the Hong Kong Island's Peak was sold for 265
million HK dollars, 90 million HK dollars more than the 175
million HK dollars at the opening of the bidding.
</P>
<P>
Land lots at Kwai Chung and Tai Po in the "New Territories"
were sold respectively for 470 million HK dollars and 44 million
HK dollars, as against the 275 million HK dollars and 16.8 million
HK dollars at the opening.
</P>
<P>
Property market analysts called the land auction promising and
noted bidders, mainly small and medium developers, showed great
interest and confidence in the market potential of the luxury
residential lots.
</P>
<P>
Stricken by the Asian financial crisis, the price of luxury
residential sites in Hong Kong once dropped dramatically, but it
began to rise again with the recovery of the local economy, said
Charles Lai, a property strategy consultant with the Surpass
Company Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some plots were sold at higher prices than the market
expectation and the site at Kwai Chung, for instance, was sold for
a price some 20 percent above the estimated 350 million-400
million HK dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The land sales, a traditional major source of government
revenue, was suspended at the end of last June. The government
resumed the land auction this year and raised nearly 1.49 billion
HK dollars from the April 20 land sales.
</P>
<P>
A government official with the Lands Department expressed
satisfaction with the results of the land auction and said the
sales were successful. 
</P>
</TEXT>
