<HEADLINE> China to Close Down Profitless Coal Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 29 (Xinhua)-- Forty loss making coal mines are
to be closed down in China this year because of the poor quality
of their product, the Director of the State Administration of Coal
Industry Zhang Baoming has announced at a coal mine directors
meeting held here recently.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, 14 coal mining companies will be declared bankrupt
which Zhang Baoming says have no reasonable prospect of ever
becoming profitable even though they have an annual production
capacity of 39.4 million tons of coal.
</P>
<P>
Over 50 million tons of coal was produced by the country's
unprofitable mines last year and these are being targeted in the
closure program.
</P>
<P>
These coal mines incurred a loss of 3.5 billion yuan (422
million US dollars) last year and the administration has taken
these drastic steps to try and pull the coal industry out of red.
</P>
<P>
China's total coal output last year was 1.25 billion tons.
</P>
</TEXT>
