<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 29 (Xinhua)-- Tianjin, North China's biggest port,
exported 2.58 billion US dollars worth of goods during the January-
May period, 24.1 percent up over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The city's total foreign trade volume in the five months
amounted to 4.86 billion US dollars, up 20 percent. The city's
imports rose 15.6 percent to 2.27 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A city official in charge of foreign trade said that the city's
foreign-funded enterprises exported 1.85 billion US dollars, an
increase of 26 percent while state-owned enterprises saw their
exports rise by some ten percent.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electronics products led Tianjin's export league,
with an export of 1.31 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
