<HEADLINE> Posts and Telecommunications Industry Enjoys Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua)-- China's posts and
telecommunications sector recorded a total business volume of 123.
5 billion yuan during the January-May period, up 32 percent on the
1998 period, according to the Ministry of Information Industry.
</P>
<P>
The business volume for the nation's postal sector grew six
percent in the period at 7.17 billion yuan, with the figure for
the telecommunications sector surging 34 percent to 116.33 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
A recent ministry report said the postal service has gained
momentum since February, with express deliveries growing by 19.6
percent and postal savings by 19.2 percent on the previous year's
period.
</P>
<P>
The report noted rate reduction during the five month period
attracted 9.24 million new telephone subscribers and 7.09 million
mobile phone users. 
</P>
</TEXT>
