<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Electronics Sector Reports Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua)-- The industrial output value for
China's electronics sector hit 240.3 billion yuan for the January-
May period, up 25.7 percent on the 1998 period.
</P>
<P>
The state sector recorded an industrial output value of 115.19
billion yuan, up 33.6 percent, accounting for 48 percent of the
nation's electronics industrial output value.
</P>
<P>
The January-April sales income for the state sector jumped 23.9
percent to 40.3 billion yuan, with profits surging 75.7 percent to
1.53 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The electronics sector reported 1,325 money-losing companies by
the end of April, up 28 on the 1998 period. Related companies had
combined losses of 1.68 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The electronics industry ended the period with stockpiles
valued at 37.7 billion yuan, an increase of 1.63 billion yuan on
the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
