<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Protests France's Delivery of War Machines to Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- India has lodged a protest to France
for delivering eight Mirage jet fighters and a submarine to
Pakistan in accordance with a 1996 contract, said Indian Defense
Minister George Fernandes on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the French daily Le Figaro published on
Tuesday, the Indian minister said that the Indian government
considered the move by France as a "grave error".
</P>
<P>
The minister said that India and France have common defense
interests. By giving dangerous weapons to Pakistan, France
committed a grave error.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that Pakistan is "an irresponsible country" which
has lost three wars to India in the past decades. In case of a
fourth war, it may push on the nuclear button, said the Indian
minister.
</P>
<P>
India and Pakistan have been fighting each other for seven
weeks over Kashmir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
