<DOCNO> XIE19990629.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-President Hu Reaffirms China's Policy, Basic Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
said here Tuesday that everything can be properly handled in Hong
Kong as long as the "one country, two systems" policy and the
Basic Law are upheld.
</P>
<P>
Hu, arriving here Tuesday morning from Shenzhen to attend the
celebrations of the second anniversary of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), made the remarks Tuesday afternoon
when he met with local public figures including Hong Kong deputies
to the National People's Congress (NPC) and members of the
National Committee of Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
"As long as we proceed from upholding the 'one country, two
systems' policy and the Basic Law, from maintaining the long-term
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong and from safeguarding the
fundamental interests of Hong Kong compatriots, we can reach the
broadest possible consensus and handle everything well in Hong
Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president said that, with the support of the central
government, the policies of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong" and a high degree of autonomy have
been fully implemented since the establishment of the SAR two
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Neither has Hong Kong's social and economic system changed, nor
has its way of living, and the laws in Hong Kong remain basically
intact, Hu commented.
</P>
<P>
Particularly, he said, the SAR government has adopted a series
of effective measures to cope with the shocks of the Asian
financial crisis and has successfully maintained the linked
exchange rate and stabilized the financial market.
</P>
<P>
"This proves that Hong Kong's economic and financial system is
sound and healthy, that the administration of the SAR government
led by Mr. Tung Chee Hwa is effective, and that Hong Kong people
are capable of managing Hong Kong," Hu commented.
</P>
<P>
Practice also "proves the correctness of the great concept of '
one country, two systems'," he added.
</P>
<P>
The pursuance of the "one country, two systems" policy and the
maintenance of Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, Hu said, are
in the fundamental interests of China and Hong Kong and also in
the interests of those countries and regions having trade and
economic activities in Hong Kong and foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president praised the Hong Kong NPC deputies and CPPCC
members and other public figures for their contributions to Hong
Kong's prosperity and stability as well as to the cause of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed those at the meeting on the economic situation
in China's mainland areas.
</P>
<P>
On hand were Fok Ying Tung, vice-chairman of the National
Committee of the CPPCC, Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region, and Liao Hui, director of the
Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
