<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 74.8
points, or 0.54 percent, to close at 13,765.49 Tuesday while China
plays maintained the momentum of increase.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover was a robust 10.803 billion HK dollars (1.
385 billion U.S. dollars), 4.147 billion HK dollars (532 million U.
S. dollars) more than that of Monday.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares continued to gain as the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations
Index increased 5.43 percent and 3.52 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The share prices rose 65.39 points, or 0.47 percent, to open at
13,905.68 Tuesday following the overnight rally of Wall Street and
finished the morning session at 13,840.88.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng index rose 55.78 points, or 0.4 percent, to close
at 13,840.29 Monday. 
