<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blueprint of Macao Handover Building Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Handover Ceremony Coordination
Office of the Macao government on Tuesday unveiled the blueprint
of a temporary structure for the handover ceremony around the
midnight of December 19.
</P>
<P>
Covering more than 6,000 square meters of floor space and
standing with a maximum height of 20 meters, the structure will be
able to hold up to 2,500 people.
</P>
<P>
In addition to a large auditorium for the ceremony signifying
China's resumption of the exercise of its sovereignty over Macao,
there will be supportive facilities, rooms for high-ranking
dignitaries and press areas.
</P>
<P>
The inside of the building will be dominated by the stage area
where dignitaries from Portugal and China will be seated. There
will be large flagpoles nearby for the formal exchange of national
flags.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of other countries and international
organizations and other guests will be seated in different
sections of the auditorium whose layout will resemble a giant
lotus flower.
</P>
<P>
As the ceremony will be held at midnight, translucent materials
will be used for the roof and part of the side walls. The entire
structure will seem brilliant in the shape of a huge Chinese
lantern.
</P>
<P>
Relevant foundation work started in early May and was completed
a few days ago. Construction of the structure will be launched
within the coming days and is expected to be finished at the end
of October.
</P>
<P>
Interior decoration and equipment installation will be carried
out in November. By early December, the entire building will be
ready for tests and rehearsals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
