<HEADLINE> America Trip Improves Understanding on HK: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Administrative
Secretary Anson Chan said here Tuesday that her recent trip to
North America has helped improve the understanding on Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Chan, who visited the United States, Canada and Mexico in the
past two weeks, told reporters that this visit has "improved the
understanding between government officials, the business community
and politicians as regard Hong Kong's present day situation."
</P>
<P>
"I hope very much that on the basis of this visit, business
people will see opportunities for them to invest further in Hong
Kong."
</P>
<P>
Chan said her visit to Washington gave her an opportunity to "
defend Hong Kong against the criticism in the Cox Report."
</P>
<P>
"I have personally met with Mr. Cox and I have invited him to
Hong Kong to see for himself our export control regime. He
acknowledged himself that we have a first grade export control
regime," Chan said.
</P>
<P>
Chan said her impression is that "there remains considerable
support for and good will toward Hong Kong," which demands that
the Special Administrative Region government continue to work hard
to earn that degree of support and respect.
</P>
<P>
"As our two largest trading partners, clearly any tension in
the relationship between America and China does have a direct
impact on Hong Kong. And I very much hope that it will be possible
within a very short period of time for that relationship, that
constructive engagement to be put on track," she said.
</P>
<P>
"We feel that this will be beneficial not only to the two
nations involved, but also will be beneficial to Hong Kong and to
the world at large," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
