<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Bandaranaike Kumaratunga will start a four-day state visit to
Nepal on July 5 at the invitation of Nepali King Birendra, the
Nepali Foreign Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
King Birendra will meet the president on July 5 and Nepali
Prime Minister Krishna Prasad Bhattarai will call on her the same
day, the ministry said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Madhav Kumar Nepal, leader of the main opposition Communist
Party of Nepal (Unified Marxist-Leninist, CPN-UML), and President
of the ruling Nepali Congress Girija Prasad Koirala will call on
Kumaratunga on July 6, the ministry said.
</P>
