<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Introduce Large Par Value Naira Notes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian government Monday approved
 the introduction of three new naira denominations of 100 , 200
and 500 naira (one U.S. dollar equals about 95 naira).
</P>
<P>
The new notes are expected to come into circulation before the
end of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to The Guardian, a leading newspaper in Nigeria, the
100 naira denomination is to bear the portrait of Chief Obafemi
Awolowo, the first premier of the defunct Western Region while
the 200 naira is to wear that of Sir Ahmadu Bello, the Sardauna of
Sokoto and the first premier of the Northern Region.
</P>
