The 500 naira note is to bear the portrait of the Owelle of
Onitsha,  Nnamdi Azikiwe, the first premier of the Eastern
Region.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Nigeria's official Television the Nigeria
 Television Authority (NTA) news Monday as saying approval of
other denominations is to follow later.
</P>
<P>
The largest par value denomination currently in circulation is
the 50 naira note.
</P>
<P>
It often requires to carry a bag of naira in order to pay the
phone bills or go shopping. 
