<HEADLINE> India, Pakistan Urged to Keep Restraint and Calm, FM Spokeswoman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China sincerely hopes that India
and Pakistan can resolve their dispute by peaceful means in order
to safeguard stability in South Asia and it urges the two
countries to maintain restraint and calmness, Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue said here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
She made the remark at a regular press conference when asked
about the military conflict in Kashmir between India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said, as a close neighbor in South Asia, China has paid
considerable attention to the conflict between India and Pakistan.
She described both as "important countries" on the sub-continent,
adding that both "have responsibilities for maintaining regional
peace and stability."
</P>
<P>
Particular efforts should be made to avoid the escalation of
the situation, she stressed.
</P>
<P>
China has always adopted an independent foreign policy of peace
and is dedicated to safeguarding and promoting peace and stability
in the South Asia, she noted, adding that China will as usual play
its due part in the regard.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif's on-going
China visit, Zhang said that Sharif began a working visit to China
starting on June 28 at the invitation of Chinese Premier Zhu
Rongji.
</P>
<P>
During Sharif's visit, leaders of the two countries exchanged
views on bilateral ties and regional and global issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
This is part of high-level reciprocal visits between the two
countries, she said. She believed the visit will further promote
the existing Sino-Pakistani friendly and cooperative ties, Zhang
said.  
</P>
