<HEADLINE> FM Spokeswoman Says Nansha Islands Sovereignty Indisputable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang
Qiyue said here today that Chinese sovereignty over the Nansha
Islands and adjacent waters is indisputable.
</P>
<P>
Zhang made the remarks at today's press conference in response
to a question about recent reports that Malaysia has built
facilities on the Yuya Shoal and Boji Reef in China's Nansha
Islands.
</P>
<P>
"Building facilities on those shoals and reefs in the Nansha
Islands under whatever excuse by relevant countries violates China
's territorial sovereignty and is illegal and invalid," she
stressed.
</P>
<P>
She said China officially notified Malaysia on May 18, to
correct the mistake and stop violating China's territorial
sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has always committed itself to stability
in the South China Sea. "We strongly demand that relevant
countries stick to the principles of the joint statement issued by
Chinese and ASEAN leaders in 1997," she added.
</P>
<P>
She urged the relevant parties to stop any action that would
possibly magnify what was going on, and to jointly safeguard the
stability of the South China Sea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
