<HEADLINE> Hainan Steps Up Anti-Drug Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Police in China's southernmost
island province have intensified their efforts in combating drug
trafficking this year and cracked or foiled 638 attempts.
</P>
<P>
They have arrested 1,476 suspected drug traffickers and
confiscated 6,710 grams of heroin since the start of this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the police department also carried out anti-drug
education campaigns in villages, farms, and schools, involving 2.5
million people. Thanks to their efforts 1,242 drug addicts have
been forced to receive treatment in drug-rehabilitation centers.
</P>
<P>
There are 17 such centers in the province and the largest in
this provincial capital of Haikou can accommodate more than 200
people. So far, it has treated 3,000 drug sufferers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
