<HEADLINE> FM Spokeswoman on US-Japan Missile Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China is concerned about the
possible signing of Memorandum of Understanding between the United
States and Japan on the development of the Theater Missile Defense
(TMD) system, according to Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman
Zhang Qiyue.
</P>
<P>
"China has several times made clear its position on the joint
development of TMD between U.S. and Japan," she said at a regular
press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
"China holds that such a move goes against the general trend of
the relaxed situation which has existed in this region since the
end of the Cold War," she noted, adding that it may also impair
the balance of the regional security and trigger a new round of
arms race.
</P>
<P>
She said this action will certainly further cause some worry
and vigilance in China and amongst other related countries and
their peoples. 
</P>
