<HEADLINE> Philippines Plans to List Tourism-Oriented Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of the Philippine
Stock Exchange (PSE) and the Department of Tourism (DOT) met
Tuesday to discuss the possibility of listing tourism-oriented
businesses nationwide.
</P>
<P>
The meeting could probably lead to the forging of an agreement
to  enhance the local capital market industry in the country, the
Philippine News Agency quoted Jose Alcantara, PSE vice president,
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Once a private company is listed with the PSE, it becomes the
property of shareholders who vote for and decide the company's
operations and direction, he said.
</P>
<P>
The idea came about after the PSE board identified
tourism-related businesses as one big potential source of capital
to boost the development of infrastructure in areas where tourism
activities are taking place, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
