<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-29 09:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PKK Leader Sentenced to Death in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK) leader Abdullah Ocalan was sentenced to death for treason
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Ankara State Security Court gave Ocalan the death
penalty as he "betrayed the country."
</P>
<P>
In the 9th court session of the trial, Ocalan said in his final
statement that he did not accept the accusation of treason.
</P>
<P>
He said that "I believe that I struggled for the unity of the
country and for a free life. I believe that I struggled for a
democratic republic, not against republic."
</P>
<P>
"I hope that the problem, which was getting bigger by
historical mistakes, will be solved," said Ocalan, adding that "I
want this trial to contribute to this."
</P>
<P>
The PKK leader added that "I reiterate my determined words and
call for a just and honorable peace and brotherhood in the axis of
a democratic republic."
</P>
<P>
"I am calling on the humanity, state and all social powers to
undertake their responsibilities," he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that "I believe that future of the country
depends on peace, not the war. I am hailing everybody."
</P>
<P>
The court said that it decided to sentence Ocalan to capital
punishment under Article 125 of Turkish Penal Code.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was captured by Turkish special agents in Kenya in
mid-February and detained on Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near
western Turkey's province of Bursa for trials on charges of
treason and separatism.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan-led PKK has been fighting since 1984 a war for an
independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. Conflicts
between the Turkish security forces and the PKK militants have
claimed over 37,000 lives and the government held Ocalan
responsible for the deaths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
