<HEADLINE> Chinese Academy of Sciences Funds University Scholarships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS) is to spend 700,000 yuan (83,400 US dollars) every year to
provide scholarships for students at 20 Chinese universities, it
announced today.
</P>
<P>
"The first group of CAS scholarships for the 1999-2001 period
will be allocated to 400 undergraduate and graduate students at
Beijing, Qinghua, Nanjing and Fudan universities, the China
University of Science and Technology and other 15 universities,"
said Bai Chunli, vice-president of the CAS.
</P>
<P>
"The CAS will provide internships for undergraduate scholarship
winners and enroll some of them for graduate studies in the
academy," added Bai, It will also enroll some of the postgraduate
scholarship winners to study for doctorate degrees or do
postdoctoral research.
</P>
<P>
Bai explained that by establishing such scholarships, the CAS
can further improve its cooperation with universities and
cultivate more talented personnel for the country's economic
development.
</P>
<P>
The CAS now has 122 institutes which can offer masters degrees
and 104 institutes which can offer doctorate degrees with a total
number of more than 11,000 postgraduate students.
</P>
<P>
The academy has also established a special fund to support "
transient" talented personnel which include people studying for
doctorate degrees and doing postdoctoral studies and visiting
scholars and researchers at the CAS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
