<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Slightly Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 29 (Xinhua) - The Australian sharemarket
finished slightly firmer on Tuesday after a solid performance by
several blue chips pulled the market out of negative territory.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index lifted one point to 2,991.3,
up from a low of 2,976 points.
</P>
<P>
The local market hit its 3,002.1-point peak in early trade on
the back of a Wall Street rally overnight Monday where the Dow
Jones Industrial Average Index jumped 102.59 points to 10,655.15.
</P>
<P>
On the local bourse Tuesday, the all industrials index firmed
4.8 points to 5,228.1 and the all resources index eased 3.1 points
to 1,218.
</P>
<P>
Banking heavyweight National Australia Bank was among the best
performers, stacking on 50 cents or 2 percent to 25.44 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the bank index climbed 31 points to 6,599.9, with
Commonwealth Bank falling 24 cents to 24.24 Australian dollars,
ANZ firming 1.5 cents to 11.356 Australian dollars and Westpac
gaining one cent to 10.02 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 554.59 million stocks changing hands for
1.39 billion Australian dollars (917.4 million U.S. dollars).
Falling stocks outnumbered rising ones by 691 to 673 while 491
stocks remained steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
