<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Private enterprises in east China
's Zhejiang Province are set to get five billion yuan in special
loans this year to boost the sector's competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement between the Zhejiang Branch of the
Agricultural Bank of China and the Zhejiang Provincial
Administration for Industry and Commerce, the funds will mainly be
spent on innovation projects.
</P>
<P>
Well performing and creditable enterprises will get priority,
said a source with the bank.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen private enterprises have got 900 million loans from the
Agricultural Bank of China following recommendation from the
provincial administration of industry and commerce.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's private enterprises produce one third of the
provincial output, with combined registered capital standing at 87.
6 billion yuan. The total output of these enterprises topped 140.8
billion yuan for the first five months of this year, up nearly 30
percent from the same period last year.  
