<HEADLINE> Industrial Robot Center to Be Set up in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Hai'er Group, a major
electrical appliances producer based in Qingdao, a coastal city in
east China's Shandong Province, plans to establish an industrial
robot manufacturing center.
</P>
<P>
The project has already passed feasibility studies by a group
of experts organized by the Ministry of Science and Technology (
MST).
</P>
<P>
Li Jian, director of the MST's science and technology
department, said that China has put the manufacturing of
industrial robots high on its development agenda and that the Hai'
er project represents a major practical step forward.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, China has made much progress in the research
and development of robot technology over the past two decades or
so.
</P>
<P>
Hai'er set up its own robot research and development center
last year, laying a foundation for the manufacture of robots.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing center, scheduled to be operational by the
end of 2000, will concentrate on the development and production of
various types of industrial robots, such as those able to carry
cargo or conduct welding and other tasks.
</P>
<P>
Hai'er President Zhang Ruimin said that the project is aimed at
helping form a robotic industry in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
