<HEADLINE> U.S. Tightening Sensitive Technology Export to HK Unreasonable: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Senate bill to impose
controls on the exports of "sensitive US technology" to Hong Kong
is totally unreasonable and will bring negative impact on the
economic development of Hong Kong, Foreign Ministry spokeswoman
Zhang Qiyue said here today.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. congressional allegation that sensitive US technology
was being transferred from Hong Kong to China's mainland is
totally groundless, the spokeswoman said at a regular press
conference.
</P>
<P>
China asked the U.S. Congress to immediately stop such actions
destructive to the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong, she said.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that the policy of "one country, two systems," "
Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong," and a high degree of
autonomy have been strictly implemented after Hong Kong returned
to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Central Government and central departments
stationed in Hong Kong, including the PLA garrison forces, have
also strictly abided by the basic law and other laws of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), and that is the fact
known to all, she said.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR Government has always imposed strict
restrictions and effective supervision on the import and export of
strategic goods, and has maintained good record, the spokeswoman
pointed out.  
</P>
</TEXT>
