<HEADLINE> NPC Law Explanation Serves Hong Kong's Interests, Spokeswoman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Explanation of the related
articles of the Hong Kong Basic Law by the Chinese National People
's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee conforms to China's
constitution and to the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR itself,
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue stated at a press
conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Asked to comment on the statement of a spokesman of the U.S.
Department of State that NPC's explanation would produce potential
impact on the judicial independence in Hong Kong, Zhang said that
the explanation is "necessary and appropriate".
</P>
<P>
She added that the explanation conforms to the original purpose
of the legislation, serves the comprehensive interest of Hong Kong
and the aspiration of Hong Kong residents.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman emphasized that the explanation would not
affect the independence of the legal and judicial systems there,
and in fact better serve the implementation of the principles of
the "One country, two systems", Hong Kong people governing Hong
Kong and a high degree of autonomy in Hong Kong, as well as
safeguard and promote the long-term prosperity and stability in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The Hong Kong affair is entirely China's internal affair,
which brooks no foreign interference," Zhang stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
