<HEADLINE> Seminar on El Nino, La Nina Phenomena Held in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A three-day seminar on the impact of
the climatic phenomena of El Nino and La Nina started here at the
Macao Meteorological and Geophysical Services on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is aimed at reviewing the impact of the two
climatic phenomena on the region of the Typhoon Committee, whose
members include 14 countries and territories frequently affected
by violent tropical hurricanes.
</P>
<P>
With the help of the seminar, these countries and territories
will become more aware of the phenomena, conduct relevant
prevention and explore ways to minimize and mitigate the impacts
of the severe climatic events, said Fong Soi Kun, director of the
Macao Meteorological and Geophysical Services.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by the World Meteorological
Organization and the Economic and Social Commission for Asia and
the Pacific, which jointly set up the Typhoon Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
