<HEADLINE> Macao Governor to Leave for Lisbon for Work Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
will leave Macao on July 2 for a visit to Estonia before heading
for Lisbon to report his work to Portuguese leaders, sources with
the governor's office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The governor will pay a visit to Estonia from July 3 to 5 at
the invitation of Estonian Prime Minister Mart Siimann.
</P>
<P>
In Lisbon, he will meet with Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio
and Foreign Minister Jaime Gama. The governor is scheduled to
return to Macao on July 12.
</P>
