<HEADLINE> Vice-President Hu Jintao in Hong Kong for Anniversary Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
arrived here from Shenzhen Tuesday morning to attend an unveiling
ceremony of the Reunification Monument scheduled for July 1.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit to Hong Kong by the Chinese vice-
president since the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR)two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Hu told reporters upon arrival that he is "happy to join the
celebrations of the second anniversary of Hong Kong's return to
the motherland" and asked the media to convey his best wishes to
the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
Hu said he expects to exchange views with Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa on issues related to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Those who greeted Hu at Lok Ma Chau checkpoint included Tung,
Administrative Secretary Anson Chan, Acting Financial Secretary
Rafael Hui, and Justice Secretary Elsie Leung.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the vice-president on the visit are Liao Hui,
director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State
Council, and Chen Fujin, deputy director of the General Office of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, President Jiang Zemin led a Chinese government
delegation to Hong Kong to attend the ceremony marking the return
of Hong Kong to China. Last year Jiang was present at the
celebrations of the first anniversary of the establishment of the
SAR. Today, Hu is here to attend the ceremony to unveil the
Reunification Monument.
</P>
<P>
All these are viewed as a support of the central government to
the SAR government and a symbol of China's confidence in
maintaining long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Also greeting the vice-president were Zheng Guoxiong, deputy
director of Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch, Ma Yuzhen,
Commissioner of the Chinese Foreign Ministry in the SAR, and Xiong
Ziren, commander of the Chinese People's Liberation Army Forces in
the SAR.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day stay here, Hu is scheduled to meet with
noted figures from various circles and attend activities arranged
by the SAR government.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President Hu Jintao flew to Shenzhen from Beijing Monday
afternoon. Upon his departure from Shenzhen, he was seen off by
local leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
