<HEADLINE> Major China Car Manufacturer Listed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Automotive Xiali Co.
Ltd. on Monday made an initial offering of 218 million A shares on
the Shenzhen Stock Exchange, one of the only two bourses in China.
</P>
<P>
The company's stock was priced at 6 yuan per share yesterday.
The issue is expected to accumulate 1.28 billion yuan for the
company's expansion and technological upgrading program.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, all of China's five major car producers have become
listed. The two exchanges in Shanghai and Shenzhen have registered
24 automobile producers. Insiders announced that the capital
market has played a more important role in upgrading China's
automobile products.
</P>
<P>
The Xiali company, based in the north China city of Tianjin,
has grabbed 20 percent of the domestic car market, in which 510,
000 China-made cars were sold last year. It produced 100,000 cars
and sold 99,800 of them in 1998. Some 40 percent of taxis in China
are Xiali-branded cars.
</P>
<P>
The board of the company yesterday disclosed its forecast for
this year's revenue at 703 million yuan, up 5 percent on last year.
It also expects to sell 150,000 cars next year, which will mean 25
percent of the market at that time.
</P>
<P>
According to stock experts, China's car industry is
experiencing fiercer competition with last year's capacity
reaching 850,000 units. Meanwhile, car imports have brought even
heavier pressures on the market, which has been attributed to the
dropping of tariffs on finished car imports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
