<HEADLINE> Guilin Hosts More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Guilin, a well-known tourist city
in southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, received 3.
42 million visitors in the first five months of this year, up 8.6
percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Tourism revenues totaled 1.33 billion yuan, up 12 percent and
the number of overseas tourists surged by 53.9 percent to reach
211,000.
</P>
<P>
The city has been increasing its attractiveness for overseas
and domestic tourists by providing better services and developing
new scenic spots in the past few years, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
Longsheng County, for example, has become a new tourist
attraction thanks to the development of local forest and folklore
resources, hosting more than 140,000 tourists in the five-month
period. 
