<HEADLINE> FM Spokeswoman Denies Milosevic Seeking Asylum in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- China has today denied the report
that Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic has sought political
asylum in China, and a FM spokeswoman has described the report as
groundless.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue made the
statement during a routine press conference Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"I have also read the report, but it is groundless," Zhang said.
</P>
