<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijingers Participate in Anti-Drug Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Public Security Bureau
cracked over 500 cases of drug abuse and trafficking involving
some 85,000 grams of illegal substances and arrested over 600
individuals between April 15-May 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
An investigation conducted between April 28-May 2 led to
ultimate arrest of three drug dealers who had swallowed 200
capsules of 1,000 grams of heroin in order to transfer the stuff.
</P>
<P>
On May 18, law enforcement officers arrested gang members and
confiscated 370 grams of drugs, two handguns, 86 rounds of
ammunition and over 5,000 yuan (600 U.S. dollars) in cash.
</P>
<P>
Neighborhood committees have assisted local government efforts
to supervise and rehabilitate drug addicts since May 1998. Related
committees counseled and introduced 317 drug addicts to
rehabilitation programs during the period.
</P>
<P>
Public security officials note that 1,557 drug addicts were
undergoing rehabilitation therapy as of June 15.
</P>
<P>
"Drugs are the source of all evil. College students have the
responsibility to warn people of the dangers involved in taking
drugs." according to a college student at the Agricultural
University of China. The student made the comments during a visit
to drug information center which has attracted 50,000 since its
establishment on May 20.
</P>
<P>
The local government has intensified efforts to inform
teenagers of the dangers and pitfalls of drug addiction. Teenagers
currently account for a large proportion of the total number of
drug addicts.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, the United Nations designated June 26 as the annual "
International Day Against Drug Abuse and Trafficking." 
</P>
</TEXT>
