<HEADLINE> Shanghai Lowers Housing Loan Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
industrial and commercial city, recently introduced interest rate
cuts for housing loans in a bid to further spur the sluggish local
real estate market.
</P>
<P>
A knowledgeable source with the Shanghai Branch of the People's
Bank of China, the country's central bank, said the cuts range
from 0.405 percent for one year loans and 1.17 percent for 10-year
housing loans.
</P>
<P>
All commercial banks in Shanghai have introduced individual
housing loan services this year in an effort to help local
residents fund housing purchases.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey indicated that Shanghainese are keen to
purchase housing, especially moderate, low-cost apartments.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by the Shanghai Branch of the Industrial
and Commercial Bank of China, shows that more than 80 percent of
910 respondents plan to buy housing within the next two years.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 percent of the respondents indicated they will
apply for bank loans.
</P>
<P>
Analysts point out that the survey indicates good prospects for
the future development of the local real estate market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
