<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, Russia Sign Contract on Buying 8 MIG-29s </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has signed a contract
with Russia for the procurement of eight MIG-29 aircraft under the
Military Technical Cooperation Agreement between the two
countries, the Bangladesh Observer newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of the Bangladeshi Air Staff Air Vice-Marshal Jamal Uddin
Ahmed and the leader of a Russian delegation, Vladimir P.
Vypriazhkine, signed the contract here on behalf of their
respective governments on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The contract provides for the supply of eight MIG-29 aircraft
from Russia to Bangladesh at the cost of 11 million U.S. dollars a
piece with fly-away kit.
</P>
<P>
The total FOB (free on board) price for the eight aircraft
including equipment is 115 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Training, transportation and technical services will cost about
9 million dollars. Twelve Russian experts will stay for six months
in Dhaka to provide initial assistance to the Bangladesh Air Force
personnel and 10 pilots and 70 technicians of the Bangladesh Air
Force will receive three months of training in Russia. 
</P>
