<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Hails Mercosur-EU Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua)-- Brazilian President Fernando
Cardoso on Monday hailed the inauguration of the association
between the South American Common Market (Mercosur) and the
European Union (EU) as a new page in the history of their
relations.
</P>
<P>
Opening a working meeting of the heads of state and government
from the countries of Mercosur, Chile and the EU, President
Cardoso reiterated that the start of the negotiating process for
the creation of a free trade zone between the two blocs will
represent "a qualitative jump in our relations".
</P>
<P>
Cardoso said, "We intend to lay the groundwork on Tuesday for
stronger trade ties through the opening of negotiations for a
progressive trade liberalization between Mercosur, Chile and the
EU".
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the first Latin American, Caribbean and EU Summit
that would run for two days, was to center on when the
negotiations should start on the creation of a free trade zone.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, grouping Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay with
Chile and Bolivia as associated members, and the 15-nation EU hope
to create a free trade zone by the year 2004 or 2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
