<HEADLINE> LA-EU Summit Opens in Rio de Janeiro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua)-- The first Latin American-
European Union summit opened here Monday, aiming at intensifying
cooperation and tightening inter-regional ties in political, trade,
social and cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
The summit is being attended by heads of state and government
or their representatives from 48 countries in Latin America, the
Caribbean and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The issue of establishing a free trade zone, especially between
the South American Common Market (Mercosur) and the EU, will be a
focus of the summit, the first ever held between the two
continents.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening of the summit, Brazilian President
Fernando Cardoso noted that Latin America and the European Union
share a common perspective in building an international order,
have common values and cultural inheritance, and share worries and
interests.
</P>
<P>
Europe is the Latin America's largest trading partner and
investor.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the two-day summit, the leaders will sign two
documents, the "Rio de Janeiro Declaration" and the "Action Plan",
which have been revised in the preparatory meetings over the past
three days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
