<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mercosur, Caribbean Countries Sign Memorandum to Enhance Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The South American Common
Market (Mercosur) signed a memorandum with Surinam, Guyana, and
Trinidad and Tobago here Monday to enhance economic and commercial
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The document proposes reciprocal investments, business meetings
and the exchange of information between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
It was signed at the Museum of Modern Art which will host the
first Latin American, Caribbean and European Union summit. The two-
day summit is to open Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, the largest trade bloc in South America, and the EU
planned to begin negotiations by November on an agreement of free
trade between the two trade blocs. Mercosur, created in December
1994, groups Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay. 
</P>
