<HEADLINE> Chinese 1-2 Finish in Men's 3-meter Board at Swedish Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese diver Xiong Ni won the
men's 3-meter springboard gold while compatriot Yu Zhuocheng
grabbed the silver at the Swedish Cup diving meet at Ronneby on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Xiong, reigning Olympic champion in this event, scored 80
points in his last dive for a total of 708.55 points, setting a
Swedish cup record.
</P>
<P>
Yu garnered 673.40 points, followed by Mexico's Fernando Platas
in third place at 643.90.
</P>
<P>
In the preliminaries for the women's three-meter board, China's
Guo Jingjing and Zhang Jing produced stable performance to rise to
the first two positions with 312.35 and 282 points respectively.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said the Swedish Cup was a world class meet as major
diving stars were competing at the southeastern city Ronneby
except Russian all-round diver Dmitry Sautin. 
