<HEADLINE> Chinese Edition of Top Encyclopedia Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The 20-volume Chinese Edition of
the Encyclopedia Britannica International has been published by
the Encyclopedia Britannica Incorporation and the Publishing House
of Chinese Encyclopedia, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The new encyclopedia is a revised and updated edition of the
Chinese Concise Encyclopedia Britannica which was translated from
the Micropaedia of the 15th edition of the Encyclopedia Britannica
and published in 1986.
</P>
<P>
The encyclopedia has taken more than 300 scholars across China
to translate and proof-read, said Xu Weizeng, chairman of the
Board of Editors of the encyclopedia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the encyclopedia has been expanded to cover major
social, economic and technological developments of the past decade,
according to the newspaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
