<HEADLINE> Vietnam Aims to Export 4 Million Tons of Rice This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is trying to boost its rice
exports with an aim to export between 3.8 million to 4 million
tons of rice this year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's English daily Vietnam News said on Tuesday that
Vietnam has already exported 2.2 million tons of rice this year at
a price of about 228 U.S. dollars per ton, the lowest in the past
five years. The largest amount of exporting was recorded from
March to June during harvest time.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with local authorities from Ho Chi Minh City and
the Mekong provinces in Ho Chi Minh City on Saturday, Deputy Prime
Minister Nguyen Cong Tan put rice exports in the last six months
at 1.6 million to 1.8 million tons against this year's target of
3.8 million to 4 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam produced a good winter-spring grain crop, with a total
yield of more than 15 million tons harvested across the country.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Mekong Delta now has some 3.3 million tons of rice
available for export, said officials of the Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development.
</P>
<P>
Tan said the government would make efforts to further simplify
rice export procedures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
