<HEADLINE> Mercosur-EU Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua)-- Heads of state or government
of the South American Common Market (Mercosur) and the European
Union (EU) met Monday to discuss the date for future negotiations
on creating a free-trade zone between the two blocs, according to
sources present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting took place before the two-day Latin America-EU
summit to open here in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur member states Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay and Paraguay
as well as Chile, an associate member, and Leaders from the 15-
member European Union, except Britain, attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The trade zone is expected to be in place in 2004 or 2005.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur countries prefer to start eliminating trade barriers
later than July 1, 2001 as proposed by the European Union.
</P>
</TEXT>
