<HEADLINE> ICBC Helping Relocation of Enterprises in Three Gorges Dam Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial Bank
of China (ICBC), one of China's four state banks, will help the
relocation of industrial enterprises in the Three Gorges Dam
region with a new fund.
</P>
<P>
The relocation fund for the dam project was managed by the
China Construction Bank until the State Council decided to entrust
part of the fund to ICBC's provincial branches in July this year.
</P>
<P>
"The move is to facilitate transfer of the funds to industrial
enterprises since more than 600 of the 1,000 or so enterprises in
the region have accounts at ICBC," Xie Duyang, vice president of
ICBC, was quoted by today's China Daily as saying.
</P>
<P>
ICBC has asked all its branches to manage the account in a
separate manner in a bid to guard against any diversion, Xie said,
adding that the bank will also support the readjustment of the
financial structure in the region by granting loans to enterprises
or projects showing high profitability or receiving State priority.
</P>
<P>
Outstanding loans to enterprises in the region from ICBC had
exceeded that of other banks, hitting seven billion yuan (843
million U.S. dollars) by the end of 1998, and a number of large
and medium-sized state enterprises had successfully completed
their relocation with the loans, Xie said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, the bank had extended a total of 4.3 billion
yuan (518 million U.S. dollars) and 78 million U.S. dollars in
loan to the construction of the Three Gorges Dam as well as
related projects including an airport and several highways.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
