</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italy's Ruling Center-left coalition won Italy's local
administrative elections which were held in 66 provinces and 28
provincial capitals in two rounds last Sunday and June 13, but
conceding the traditional bastion of the left, Italian central
city of Bologna, and Italian north province of Milan to the
opposing Center-right. (Italy-Local Elections) 
