<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile Seeks Solution to Pinochet Case in Rio Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Chile will seek a solution
to the Pinochet case with every effort and means, Chile's
President Eduardo Frei told Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria
Aznar here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chilean officials said that the two leaders held a meeting
prior to the inauguration of the Latin America-EU summit attended
by 48 Latin American and European leaders.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two discussed issues of common interest,
especially the case of former Chilean leader Augusto Pinochet.
</P>
<P>
Frei said that his country "will search for every solution, be
it political, juridical or humanitarian."
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was arrested in October in London at the request of
Spanish judge Baltasar Garzon, who wants to try him for the human
rights violations during his 1973-1990 term.
</P>
<P>
Frei has tried to obtain Pinochet's freedom, arguing that
Garzon's request violates Chile's sovereignty because foreign
courts have no jurisdiction over its ex-leaders.
</P>
<P>
But Aznar accepted a court ruling that the request is legal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
