<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Move Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks moved
higher Monday as investors were convinced that the Federal
Reserve would raise interest rates by only a quarter
percentage point at its meeting this week.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 102.59 at
10,655.15. The index lost 303 points last week.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 16.04 at 1,331.35 and the technology
heavy Nasdaq index rose 49.79 at 2,602.44.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve was widely expected to raise interest
rates by 0.25 percent to cool off the U.S. economy at its Open
Market Committee meeting on June 29-30. The expectation relieved
investors' worries about more increases in interest rates that
would hit the economy.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 5.55 at 628.89 and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 2.08 at 774.10.
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 5.50 at 448.61.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 12-to-7 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,862 up, 1,080 down and
573 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 641.14 million shares from 609.76
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
